########################### SQL Concepts ###########################

#### SQL statement types

1) DDL (data definition language)
	
# Define,change or drop database objects
# Common DDL statements
	1) CREATE : to create objs
	2) ALTER : alter tables and data types
	3) TRUNCATE : used for del all data in table(not to del table)
	4) DROP : to del objs

2) DML (Data manipulation language)

# read and modify data
# CRUD ops (create , read , update and delete rows)
# Common types
	# INSERT : insert >=1 rows
	# SELECT : query
	# UPDATE : edits rows
	# DELETE : remove data from rows

 

